[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jon Flatt: Chesterfield sign goalkeeper from Wolves

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One side Chesterfield have added goalkeeper Jon Flatt on loan from Wolves until the end of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 20-year-old, who had a spell at Wrexham earlier this season, will join the side as cover and is available for Saturday's match with Walsall.
Meanwhile, the Spireites have recalled striker Armand Gnanduillet from his brief loan with Oxford United.
The 23-year-old Ivorian only made four appearances without scoring for the U's over a three-week period.
